On 12/9/2012 2:28 PM, Max Bronsema wrote:
> I agree with Mike. However, if you have two people use a hammer as well. My
> helper used a rubber mallet and whacked the center with the horn cap
> removed. While whacking, I pulled on the wheel and it popped right to the
> top of the nut. Then you remove the nut and wheel comes right off.

Ditto - this is exactly the way I remove it.  There's a little up-down 
play that will allow the shaft to be driven downwards.  Just make sure 
you loosen the nut first ;)
